I noticed another comment of yours from a few hours ago with a question. Seems the comment is gone? 
Did you manage to get through the bug or still need help?

Try this in your code: 

use: {
          loader: "file-loader",
          options: {
            esModule: false,
            name: "[name].[hash].[ext]",
            outputPath: "imgs"
          }
    }

Notice *esModule: false*

It was a bug that got fixed that got fixed a few days ago. 
The default setting is *esModule: true* and that will give you something like: *<img src="[object Module]" />* inside your index.html (in your dist folder). 
Hence, you have to set *esModule: false* in your webpack.common.js
